data.description: A cute 3BR/2BA pool home nestled on a quiet cul-de-sac street in St. Augustine Shores. Set back from the street there's a deep front yard with abundant sunshine hoping for a gardener or a game of catch. Inside, 1,800sf open plan keeps it simple with ample wall space for furniture groupings and plenty of natural light. The living and dining room flow together seamlessly so everyday living is as easy as throwing a party. The kitchen offers white shaker cabinets, granite counters and stainless appliances and it is conveniently hidden from view at the front door but directly across from the dining room so it's just steps back and forth from stove to table when you are not dining poolside or al-fresco on the deck. There’s a office/den off the kitchen and two sets of doors off the dining and living rooms that open to a step-down Florida room with large sliding windows and beautiful views of the pool. Two bedrooms and a shared bath flank the front hall with the master suite tucked to the back. The en-suite master offers a spacious bedroom and its corner location allows for additional windows and fills the room with great natural light. Outside, enjoy summer days in the pool, afternoons in the hot tub or evenings around the firepit. Your four-legged friends will enjoy exploring the yard and there is a tree house for the kids to enjoy too. The shed has room to store the tools and toys, raised garden boxes ready for you to make your own, and don’t forget to rinse the sand and salt off in the outdoor shower. The St. Augustine Shores community has 58 acres of parks & 45 acres designated recreational sites on the Intracoastal. From the house you can enjoy walking, biking, or jogging through miles of bike paths, sidewalks, and 14 lakes/ponds. There is a 12,000 sq ft recreation building known as the Riverview Club with a large pool, a kiddie park, picnic area, horseshoe pit, volleyball and sports field. The Riverview Club houses a ballroom, game room, library and kitchen facilities available for rent. There is also a pier with a gazebo that extends into the Intracoastal and is perfect for anglers and wildlife observers. For golfers, there is the St. Augustine Shores Golf Club. Enjoy…
